  "text": "The FxVanillaOption type family in OpenGamma Strata is comprehensively traced across the multi-module Maven project. The 4 core Joda-Beans domain classes are located in modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/: FxVanillaOption (line 37), FxVanillaOptionTrade (unresolved type), ResolvedFxVanillaOption (unresolved type), and ResolvedFxVanillaOptionTrade (unresolved type). These represent the product definition and its trade wrapper, along with their resolved variants used during calculation. The pricer classes in modules/pricer/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/pricer/fxopt/ implement two pricing methodologies: BlackFxVanillaOptionProductPricer and BlackFxVanillaOptionTradePricer using the lognormal Black model, and VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionProductPricer and VannaVolgaFxVanillaOptionTradePricer using the smile-based Vanna-Volga method. Note: Unlike FxSingleBarrierOption which supports Black and ImpliedTrinomialTree variants, FxVanillaOption only supports Black and Vanna-Volga methods as confirmed in FxVanillaOptionMethod enum. The measure calculation classes in modules/measure/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/measure/fxopt/ include FxVanillaOptionMeasureCalculations (final class for internal use), FxVanillaOptionTradeCalculationFunction (public class implementing the calculation function interface), FxVanillaOptionTradeCalculations (public class for trade-level calculations), and FxVanillaOptionMethod (enum specifying the available pricing methods: BLACK and VANNA_VOLGA). The FxVanillaOptionTradeCsvPlugin (modules/loader/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/loader/csv/) provides CSV loading functionality for FxVanillaOptionTrade objects. The FxSingleBarrierOption class (modules/product/src/main/java/com/opengamma/strata/product/fxopt/) embeds FxVanillaOption as a dependency via the underlyingOption field (line 59), representing a barrier option built on top of a vanilla FX option."
}

